  "prompt": "I never write lyrics before, how to write song lyrics?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for writing song lyrics:\n\n1. Start with a theme or emotion\n- Choose a topic you're passionate about\n- Draw from personal experiences\n- Explore feelings like love, heartbreak, hope, etc.\n\n2. Brainstorm and freewrite\n- Write down ideas without judging them\n- Use stream of consciousness\n- Let your thoughts flow freely\n\n3. Structure your lyrics\n- Typical song structure: Verse - Chorus - Verse - Chorus - Bridge\n- Chorus should be catchy and memorable\n- Use repetition for emphasis\n\n4. Use poetic techniques\n- Metaphors and similes\n- Rhyming (optional)\n- Imagery\n- Rhythm and flow\n\n5. Be honest and authentic\n- Write from the heart\n- Don't be afraid to be vulnerable\n- Tell a story or express genuine emotions\n\n6. Practice and revise\n- First drafts are rarely perfect\n- Read your lyrics out loud\n- Get feedback from others\n- Experiment with different approaches\n\n7. Learn from other songwriters\n- Study lyrics of songs you enjoy\n- Analyze their structure and techniques\n- Practice by writing in different styles\n\n8. Experiment with songwriting tools\n- Rhyming dictionaries\n- Songwriting apps\n- Collaborating with musicians\n\nRemember, there's no single \"right\" way to write lyrics. Practice and find your unique voice.",
